text:
my trigger was a news article. the rape victim was only 8 months old. i have a 20 month old daughter myself and i realised something important. for 20 years i was sexually assaulted by three different relatives. only seven when it first happened, i don't remember details but i can feel the fear, the uneasiness and most of all the hatred still sitting inside me. when i told my mom i was discouraged to talk about it. i later found out my younger sister was sexually assaulted too. sadly the first thing a victim often hears is “don't tell anyone, it will ruin your reputation” or “you should have been more careful”. sex education should be taught at both school and home. but here it’s a big 'no-no'. however i promise to educate and always listen to my daughter and will do whatever it takes to normalise sexual abuse and call out victim shaming.  for her i’m confronting my past to protect her future.
.
.
#nasdaily #nasdailyglobal #metoo #metoomovement #speakup #breakthesilence

over 25,000 pages are written each day on @wikipedia, yet, only 17% of profiles are of women! 
let's add more stories about overlooked women to honor their amazing achievements.

on international women's day (8 march), join @unesco and @wikimedia for our global edit-a-thon #wiki4women.

register online now! for more info, click on the link in our bio.

“honestly, i can't really stop thinking about the migrant caravan at the us-mexican border, and the family separation. it has also made me step back and recognize my own privilege in the world. through no doing of my own, simply because of where i was born and the family that i was born into, i have been afforded so many more opportunities. that recognition has made me think different about my fellow citizens -- about how i treat others and can use my privilege to benefit those who are unfairly held down.”
_
“the "me too" movement has really caused more discussion about how women are treated in the world. over the last year or so, i have found that men have started to believe the stories of my experiences. in the past, i found that they would excuse them or write them off as an exception instead of the rule. they didn't want to believe that their life and their opportunities were easier than mine. now, i find that more men are willing to listen and are even starting to advocate for women in spaces where they are not present.”
_
“recently, our family’s adoption went through and we have a beautiful son that we are so in love with, it hurts. through the process we talked a lot about trans-racial families to our family and friends. i have seen that a lot of the news stories about people of color being assaulted, killed, or mistreated has helped to underline that racism is still a reality. it's supported by the fact that just because that hasn't been our reality, doesn't mean it isn't the truth for others. i have seen our friends and family start to call out behaviors and micro-aggressions, and stop using some of the racial language that didn't seem like a big deal before. it gives me hope that our son won't have to deal with some of what we are seeing today.”
_
“by definition, being a citizen means that you live within specific borders, but i'd like to think that being a citizen goes a little deeper. to me, it means being an engaged, active, and positive force in society. a good citizen is someone that you can count on to represent your community and have your back if need be.”

text:
era of ignition comes out in just under a week and one of the many chapters i’m excited (and quite nervous) to share with you is an intimate look at the last year and a half of america’s trajectory, starting just before 2017’s #metoo movement (originally founded over two decades ago by activist tarana burke) and the subsequent upheaval and harnessing of women’s rage into action, propelling us into different positions of power; political, professional and personal. .

from details on the formation of time’s up and those wild early months building the organization from the ground up, to my own revelations  on a severely abusive relationship in my early twenties. .

these chapters will, i hope, make you feel less alone in your own fight to exist and be seen in a world that often wants individuality to be erased. #eraofignition (link in bio)

text: books of 2019: shout by laurie halse anderson. i am just in awe of anderson. i loved her and her writing when i was a teenager and i am glad that it rings true today in my 30's. when talking about her life, she doesn't mince words, she gets to the honest truth, which is raw and heartbreaking but at the same time uplifting. she talks about the aftermath of her sexual assault in excruciating detail but it's something that needed to be done. she explores the positives and the negatives of the #metoo movement and the effect it has on out current society. for a book for teens, again she doesn't handle them with kid gloves. in fact she tells them the god honest truth, something they need to hear right now. this is a book everyone, people of all ages, need to read right now. thank you edelweiss for an advanced copy for an honest review. ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐/5 #bookstagram #books #bookreview #advancedcopy #shout #speak #lauriehalseanderson #yabooks #yanonfiction #metoo #timesup #booksof2019 #cupofteajonesbooks2019

text: hi i’m sorry for posting twice in a day but we just hit 1000 streams on spotify!!! i’m so happy and grateful for this spectacular achievement that we reached in a little over 2 weeks! :) “orange.” was also something i was really apprehensive about releasing because of the subject nature and because of the nature of the recording process. i released it too quickly, i think, as part of my miss ny campaign, and while i’m glad i used it to make an impact, i wasn’t happy with the caliber of my voice on the track. not only because i was sick that day and i couldn’t reschedule, but i also really rushed to get this recording out under he time constraints of that competition and, well,  i paid a small price for that and it wasn’t really worth it for that event... but ya know it’s a learning experience nonetheless. 🤷🏻‍♀️🤷🏻‍♀️🤷🏻‍♀️ despite my insecurities, i’ve received nothing but positive feedback and support from this piece, and i’m grateful. thank you so much for listening and supporting a local sad boi like me, i wanted this piece to be impactful and the numbers are showing me it just might be doing some good. the intent was to make people understand, and to empathize with others like myself who have struggled, and i think we really did that here. additionally, the people who worked on this project are special to me, and it meant the world to me that we all collaborated on something so intimate and powerful, so thank you guys too 🧡. i love you all so much and am honored by your continuous support. please keep streaming! 🧡 (better) more music coming soon 🧡 #metoo #activisminmusic
name: Gabriella Elyse Monaco Bavaro

text:
aún estando en croacia puedo escuchar los ecos del fascismo en españa. no son nuevos pero rechinan con ciertos aires de frescura que no termino de entender.
joder, íbamos bien. 
pienso a veces.

y vamos bien.
cada vez somos más. más completas, más diversas, más tenaces.

juntas, desde varias perspectivas, ayudándonos a crecer. y eso no lo van a parar. 
lo grandioso de nuestra revolución es que supera los momentos de trompeta y de bastillas, aunque también los tengamos, para tejer con paso de yeso una nueva realidad que se fija entre las grietas de nuestra historia.

nada que temer porque estamos construyendo desde todas las esquinas y de forma transversal. déjalos que griten, que no van a pasar.

antifascistas siempre. 💜

#feminismo #feminista #antifascista #utopia #transversalidad #psicologia #psicologaonline #psicologafeminista #sororidad #metoo #niunamenos #notallmen #hastalavictoriasiempre

text:
как жить в стране, где женщиной быть опасно?
⠀
сегодня случилось то, чего я ужасно боюсь. мужчина шёл по подземному переходу, и внезапно начал приближаться ко мне и что-то шептать о моей ©ексуальности. он уверенно шёл на меня, явно проявляя агрессию и впервые в жизни я собиралась бежать. 13.00 дня. людей вокруг нет. возможно субъект находился в алкогольном  или наркотическом опьянении. я инстинктивно начала показывать ответную агрессию и отступила в сторону, ускорив шаг. мне удалось проскользнуть мимо него и рвануть наружу..
⠀
после чего я проплакала всю дорогу домой. а что было бы, если бы он на меня напал?
⠀
⠀
пришло время жутких историй из жизни, листайте карусель
⠀

.

text:
😭🦏😭⁣
⁣
one of my best friends and gypsy soul sister, janna is in africa as she is several times a year for her beautiful non-profit, re:joyce. i thought it was just one of her regular trips...little did i know that she and 5 other friends had a beautiful surprise for me. 😭😭😭😭⁣
⁣
they sponsored this 3 1/2 month old baby girl for 3 years in my name so that i can get updates on her as she grows and gets taken care of at the meru national park by the david sheldrick wildlife trust. ⁣
⁣
what an incredible and thoughtful gift...i legit can’t believe it!!! ⁣
⁣
so world, this is maarifa. she’s a 3 1/2 month old white rhino. they’ve had her since she was 3 days old and she’s bottle fed by her caretaker, omar, every 3 hours. it’s nighttime there and they have her all cuddled up ready for bed. ⁣
⁣
ladies, i can’t wait to squeeze all your necks in two weeks!!! thank y’all from the bottom of my heart! ♥️♥️♥️♥️⁣
⁣

⁣
ladies, i can’t wait to squeeze all your necks in two weeks!!! thank y’all from the bottom of my hea! ♥️♥️♥️♥️⁣
⁣

text:
book review: the women’s war by jenna glass
⭐️⭐️.5 / dnf at page 268.
—-—-—-—-—-—-—-—-—-—-—
trigger warning: misogyny/sexism, rape, violence, racism
content warning: white feminism
—-—-—-—-—-—-—-—-—-—-—
i received an advance reading copy of this book from the publisher. this in no way biased my review, which presents my honest thoughts about the book.
—-—-—-—-—-—-—-—-—-—-—
when alysoon’s disgraced mother activates a spell to free women from oppression, the whole world is shook. now, women don’t have to submit to men as they did before. thrown out of the city by the king in the aftermath, the abigails who once resided with alysoon’s mother come across a new well of power. contrarily to usual wells around which major cities are built, this one is mainly composed of female elements. plenty enough for them to work up a supply of potions and – maybe – fight back.
.
if this summmary sounds weird to you, that’s pretty much what reading this book was for me. you think “oh, feminism and fighting for equality, that’s great!” and then you read and it’s basically just the women being super happy because they can sleep with whoever they like. as long as that person is male... because there’s zero queer rep in this novel. funny enough, the author wrote an entire book (start of a trilogy) about feminism and #metoo and she didn’t ever think that it would be a good idea to include queer characters?!?!?! as you can guess, that was my main problem.
.
but that’s not the only problematic thing. her feminism is as white as it comes. no disability, no body diversity, no different social classes (all her characters are nobles) and barely any ethnic diversity. not to mention the only character with a different skin colour (shelvon is from nandel and her skin is paler than other characters) is subject to microagressions on the daily. the author tried to make up a reversed racism situation or whatever... i don’t think it ended up the way she wanted to.
.
basically, this book is just a very long series of women taking advantage of their sexual revolution. as in, it’s non-graphic sex/flirting scenes one after another. in a high fantasy setting.
reminded me why i don’t read adult fantasy...

text:
ni var många som krävde att jag skulle publicera namnet på den som våldtog mig, när jag gick ut med det i media hösten 2017.
tidningar, radio och tv ville höra alla detaljer.
inte minst svenska friidrottsförbundet ville ha namnet. och visst, de ville ha det för internt bruk, men det är inte direkt ovanligt att läckor förekommer inom större organisationer. vad hade hänt då? hade jag klarat av att stå emot alla påtryckningar från media, från privatpersoner som tyckte att jag ljög för att få uppmärksamhet, från eventuellt anhöriga till den jag pekat ut? hur hade mina barn, min man och övriga familj mått? vad hade de behövt utstå för hot och hat? hur hade min idrottskarriär påverkats?
för det är ju tydligen det som händer om man berättar offentligt om vem som har utsatt en för ett brott. man blir hotad, hatad, baktalad och förrådd av vänner, bekanta, arbetsgivare och gemene man.
jag har inte behövt uppleva det ovanstående, för jag publicerade aldrig namnet. och det skedde endast för min och min familjs skull, för jag har absolut inget att dölja.
men @cissiwallin har däremot behövt leva sig igenom alla de hemskheter jag nämnde ovan. att hon ännu står upp idag och orkar fortsätta kämpa är bortom allt förstånd. hon är en enorm förebild ♥️
läs hennes brev till granskningsnämnden i bilderna ovan, och tänk att allt hon gjorde var att berätta vem som våldtog henne.
#metoo

text:
fighting for yourself and standing up for others is always worth it but it can be exhausting and mentally draining. you know that anxiety you feel when your phone is about to die? the same thing happens to your soul when you keep pushing yourself past your limits. remember to take short breaks throughout the day to breathe and find ways to focus on the things that bring you happiness and help you recharge. keep that battery of yours out of low power mode. 💕
.
.

text:
today on our blog (link in bio) we're sharing a sneak peek at our new picture book biography of dr. maya angelou, out this fall! rise! from caged bird to poet of the people, dr. maya angelou is a gorgeous biography in verse written by award-winning biographer @bethany.hegedus and illustrated by amazing artist @tonyaengel1, with a special foreword by angelou's grandson, colin a. johnson. it looks at a life marked by transformation and perseverance, from angelou’s early days in arkansas to her later work as a freedom fighter and triumphant rise as a poet. angelou’s path out of silence after sexual assault holds a particular poignancy in the context of today’s #metoo discussions. look for it in august 2019, just in time for the 50th anniversary of i know why the caged bird sings!⁣
⁣

sometimes i have to remind myself that i need to take time for me to just sit and be in my feels. it takes a lot of discipline to get back up and start the day all over again, but we do it because life is too short.

take your day! pout, cry, drink coffee, feel those emotions. then tomorrow, get up, take a shower, look yourself in the eyes and tell yourself how much you love you and keep moving.

text:
i always think its funny when these basic quotes and mottos are painted onto walls. i've seen them from la to kl. truth be told they don't hold any real weight. there is no plan or guide. however, i sat under this one at the restaurant i was eating at today and it made me think about what it actually takes to make your dreams blossom.

dreams and goals alike take work to accomplish and reach. no one ever thought to themselves that they would be successful in anything and it happened just like that. it takes a tremendous amount of effort to get anywhere close to your dreams. it takes sacrifice and dedication and most of all it takes a willingness to sacrifice anything outside of your goal to reach them. this is just a hard truth. 
my goal for the last few years is my health. its literally taken everything for me to get healthier mentally, physically, and emotionally. in fact just two years ago i was on deaths door. what i've discovered in my journey is that it takes effort and a lot if support. i have to have both and i am so incredibly grateful. i am humbled by the fact that i have amazing friends and a support system that has seen my from my lowest low to my highest high. obviously this goes deeper still but my dreams are blossoming because of sacrifice and the willingness to do whatever it takes and knowing that i have people that have my back. i've done nothing on my own.

what are your dreams? are they comings to fruition? why or why not?

text: goodmorning. society would have me believe that i should go through life living with my eyes wide shut. little black girls should remain voiceless and silent about their narratives. instead of muting pedophiles like r. kelly, you would rather silence me because my words don’t have a catchy hook that will entice you to strip naked and make love, but instead to realize that in society black girls are in need of love. we are suffering in silence in intellectual spaces that seek to invalidate our existence and oppress our liberation with patriarchy. in classrooms black girls are being pushed out at a higher rate than our black boys. how many black women have been killed by police violence over the past few years. if i told you to name someone other than sandra bland, could you? 1 in 18 black women will be imprisoned versus 1 in 111 of their white counterparts or 1 in 45 of their latinx counterparts. in the words of dr. anna julia cooper, black women are “doubly enslaved” and have been left in a space of suffering, struggle, silence, and consequently outlet stories have gone unwritten or incomplete. it is time hold space and reclaim our voice and write our own histories. #speak #voice #poetry #write #blackgirlmagic #sayhername #black #blackgirl #culture #america #losangeles #art #blackart #metoo #ustoo #books #facts #knowledge

text:
sacrificing a lot for him didn’t make him.
going the extra mile for him didn’t make him.
giving all your love and your body to him didn’t make him.
you thought if you put you’re all into the situationship it would make him “love” you back, but nothing can.
and was it really love you were giving him or was it incentives to make him give you what you gave? 
does he even know the sacrifices you made?
____
if he doesn’t want to return what you’ve done for him then he doesn’t want to. you can’t change that! 
and you demanding that he gives this effort back is actually quite selfish of you....
you stayed there and let him suck this life and effort out of you. so the damage that has now been laid upon you didn’t come from him, it came from you...

text:
hur det känns att bli utmålad som en galen mytoman som ljugit om ett övergrepp, på bästa sändningstid i public service-tv? när man dessutom är höggravid och redan lever under hot? 
här är det jag skrivit som svar till #granskningsnämnden efter min och alla era rekordmånga anmälningar dit, om vårens #uppdraggranskning - ” #metoo och fredrik virtanen”. det är ganska långt, men vill man förstå all handmaids tale/män som hatar kvinnor-galenskap som hänt så läs gärna👆

svt må vara en jätte (som gav sig på en enskild kvinna vars ”brott” = berättat om övergrepp) men jag viker mig inte en millimeter här. 
om granskningsnämnden inte fäller svt tappar man ju tron helt på public service. men vi får bara vänta och se. nu har dom skickat detta jag skrev till svts ledning, och svar kommer inom kort.

kommer lägga upp allting, har som bekant inget alls att dölja.

text:
¿os dais cuenta de la cantidad de tabúes y prohibiciones con los que carga la mujer y su cuerpo?
•
se da por hecho y se normaliza que los hombres vean porno desde adolescentes para masturbarse, en cambio jamás siquiera se piensa en las mujeres.
•
es como si la masturbación femenina no existiera.
•
se ignora por completo la sexualidad femenina, el hecho de que el sexo pueda gustarnos, que queramos disfrutarlo libremente y con quien nos dé la gana, que nos masturbemos...
•
se da por hecho que la mujer es ese ser recatado, que no habla ni piensa en sexo, excepto cuando se encuentra con un hombre que “le enseña” a disfrutarlo.
•
y ojo, que siempre será un hombre. la posibilidad de que sea con otra mujer con quiera disfrutar del sexo tampoco se contempla, a no ser que se haga para el disfrute masculino.
•
necesitamos dejar de transmitir este tipo de tabúes. tenemos que dejar claro que esas creencias son falsas, y que por eso mismo siempre se tapan con el silencio.
•
adueñémonos de nuestros cuerpos, de nuestra sexualidad, de nuestro propio placer.

text:
my heart feels heavy. will we meet again? this moment. i can smell a whiff of the future. it whispers to me of uncertainty. of love, undeclared . of loss, that may safely return. i will pray for this, if god wills. i will look upto the sky in longing. i will wait patiently for god's answer, like the sky waits for the night to end when darkness prevails. i will see the light prevail. on the canvas that is my life, i will watch the color spread. blue, the color of love. yellow, what your laugh feels like. saffron, where our love flourished. the chirping birds? how i felt when we spent our first morning together. i will pray before i sleep, and when i wake up. i will pray for another time. when this guilt washes away. when my self respect isn't on the ground. i will pray for a time, when i look at you with contentment. i will pray for something, no matter how elementary, that lasts. i will pray for it here and in the hereafter. and when i do, i envision you in your khakis, a vest as grey as my soul, leaning against the sofa carved out of a walnut tree. i can see myself in your arms as you scroll through your feed, on a friday morning. the smell of noon chai i've made for you, and the kulch you have brought from the kandur. what a morning it would be. .
.
.
.
.
picture by @simrah_qadri .

text:
#блог
⠀
оскар – 2019
⠀
по-домашнему мило
⠀
91-я церемония вручения премии «оскар» с точки зрения победителей была ожидаемой. все фильмы, которые получили главные награды, уже имели успешную фестивальную судьбу в европе. однако несколько скандальных сюрпризов этот «оскар» все же преподнес.
⠀
итак, лучший фильм – «зеленая книга» питера фаррелли, лучший фильм на иностранном языке и лучший режиссер – «рома» и альфонсо куарон, лучшая актриса – оливия колман («фаворитка» йоргоса лантимоса) и лучший актер – рами малек («богемская рапсодия» брайана сингера). возможно, «богемская рапсосдия» стала бы и лучшим фильмом, если бы не скандал с брайном сингером из серии #metoo, который разразился еще во время вручения главной британской кинопремии bafta. картина подходила для гран-при, помимо своих высоких профессиональных достижений, и по всем параметрам политкорретности – фредди меркьюри не только звезда музыкальной сцены, но эмигрант и вич-инфицированный гей. и, возможно, «зеленая книга», помимо своих высоких профессиональных достоинств, заменила неожиданно сошедшего с дистанции почти стопроцентного лауреата тоже по политкорректным соображениям.
⠀
подробности: https://nanevskom.ru/oskar-2019/
⠀

text:
kitchen table's jennifer rossi joins the panel for this year's women's awareness week for #iwd2019 in vancouver. we are truly excited!
.
.
for jennifer rossi, the term ‘kitchen table’ represents more than simply the name of the local restaurant group she has helped steer for the past decade — it also speaks to the authentic and familial approach she takes toward work, life and community.

born and raised in vancouver, jennifer received an early education in the hospitality industry by working her way up the rungs of her grandfather’s restaurant and food-services company with roles as a line cook, host, server, bartender and manager. after two years in various front-of-house positions with cactus restaurants ltd., she added the title of owner to her resume when she co-founded kitchen table and opened the comfort-food-and-cocktail hotspot pourhouse in vancouver’s historic gastown district in 2009.

two years later, kitchen table bolstered its portfolio by setting up shop with the northern italian-focused pizzeria farina and casual italian eatery ask for luigi in 2014, which went on to win restaurant of the year, best new restaurant, best casual and best italian at the 2015 vancouver magazine restaurant awards. in 2017 the group opened st. lawrence, which won best restaurant and best new restaurant at the 2018 vancouver magazine restaurant awards and no. 4 on enroute’s list of canada’s best new restaurants.

no matter how significant the strides she continues to make with kitchen table, jennifer never forgets the core principles that were instilled in her during her formative days in the industry: putting personal and professional integrity first, treating colleagues and coworkers as you would family and fully embracing the notion that the fondest memories are made at the kitchen table.
.
. 
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10)
https://iwd2019vancouver.eventbrite.ca or the link in @minibarcanada's profile.

text:
post-traumatic stress disoreder (ptsd) adalah gangguan yang ditandai dengan kegagalan untuk pulih setelah mengalami atau menyaksikan peristiwa yang mengerikan.
_
perkosaan jelas merupakan sesuatu yang mengerikan. apalagi jika korban mengalami tonic immobility. selengkapnya pernah dibahas @jiemiardian -
kondisi ini bisa berlangsung berbulan-bulan atau bertahun-tahun, dengan pemicu yang dapat membawa kembali kenangan trauma disertai dengan reaksi emosional dan fisik yang intens.
-
gejalanya dapat mencakup mimpi buruk atau kilas balik, menghindari situasi yang mengingatkan trauma, meningkatkan reaktivitas terhadap rangsangan, kegelisahan, atau suasana hati yang tertekan.
-
penanganannya berupa berbagai jenis psikoterapi serta obat untuk mengatasi gejala.
-
perkosaan adalah fenomena gunung es. hanya sedikit yang bisa dicatat secara resmi oleh @komnasperempuan dalam catahu atau catatan tahunan yang diumumkan pada publik setiap tanggal 8 maret, hari perempuan internasional 👧👩👵 catahu komnas perempuan 2018 mencatat terdapat 348.446 kasus kekerasan terhadap perempuan, perkosaan termasuk di dalamnya.
-
kisah nyata perempuan lainnya yang tidak tercatat bisa kalian baca di @lawanpatriarki "satu lagi cerita perempuan"
-
banyak faktor kenapa korban enggan melapor, atau kalau melapor berakhir "damai" seperti kasus agni di ugm. terbaru yang saya ketahui ada warganet yang memgetik begini, "afwan, ukhti. perkosaan itu aib. allah saja menutupi aib-aibmu, kenapa engaku buka lagi dengan #beranibicara #bravetospeakup #metoo #hearmeatoo?"
-
kenapa kalian meremehkan perempuan yang berani menceritakan kisahnya? mereka perlu keberanian besar untuk bercerita. ada derai air mata dan jantung berdebar, pasti! lantas apa mau kalian? menikahkan korban perkosaan dengan pelakunya sehingga korban akan merasa terus diperkosa sepanjang hidupnya?
-
#speakup seorang perempuan berarti besar, ia akan mendorong banyak perempuan lainnya untuk bercerita. apa pentingnya bercerita? bagi sender ia akan merasakan lega. setelah ia lega, ia akan lebih midah sembuh untuk dari ptsd. saya penyintas. saya tahu rasanya :)
-
terima kasih telah membaca keresahan saya
-
sincerely yours
💞💙
@winonabd

—————————
cardinal george pell was convicted few days ago of abusing two choir boys in melbourne in 1996. to lay out certain facts: 
1. pell was widely seen as the church’s most powerful official.
2. the victims were 13 years old when the attack took place.
3. pell orally raped one of the boys forcing him to perform a blow job and squeezed hard other boys genitals while walking off.
4. these two boys, one of which passed away few years ago, got a bit of their justice at the age of 35.
that’s 22 years of mental trauma and fear that finally got justice. so many kids, even today are assault by highest order officials in church and have been facing this around the world since 1980s. it’s disgusting, outrageous and saddening. seeing george pell go to jail is reinstating the hope in justice system, but what’s most important is to believe the victims, help them through the trauma and stand with them in their fight. collectively we can be someone’s helping hand and protect our children from demons like these.
—————————

text:
ok...where to begin. i am a bridesmaid in a wedding coming up. the moh and i spent months and many many hours planning this past weekend. she arrived the day before everyone else were to arrive and spent the night at my house so we could tie up some loose ends...
.
.
.
.
fast forward to saturday night. the girls were all going to order from an italian restaurant i recommended. my husband was aware of this since i told him i’d recommended one of our favorite places. i had the flu 😡but joined them for a brief activity and then went home. he called me on my way home and said, “since you couldn’t stay for dinner there, i ordered a lot of food from the same place so you could enjoy it here.” well that was thoughtful considering my mom has been here taking care of all of us flu-y people! she deserved a nice meal more than anyone. .
.
.
upon returning home, i noticed he wasn’t kidding. he ordered a lot of food. my first question to him was, “how did you pay for this?” (i mean 👋🏻 we are always broke). he told me he found lots of promo codes. honestly, it sounded weird to me but i was too sick to dispute anything. i helped him bring the food in and made my mom eat before anyone. like i said—she deserved it and, my! what a feast we had! .
.
.
he asked me the next day how my friends enjoyed their meal that they ordered from the same place. apparently they couldn’t get delivery, so they found another italian place. when my husband looked shocked and weirded out and asked, “from where?” i simply said “idk, but the amount of garlic bread they brought these drunk chicks was hilarious.” i moved on from it. .
.
.
fast forward to tonight. my friend texted me, “i have a charge of $270 from (original italian place) and we didn’t even go there!” a normal person might have reacted, “holy shit, cancel your card and dispute the charges.” my abnormal ass instead responded, “omg. how did my husband acquire your information? you need to confirm the order so i can tell you what it is, and you then must immediately call the police if this is the case.” she texted back, “omg i was just venting but holy shit i didn’t even consider that. i was so nice to him!” (cont in comments).
name: Surviving a Narc & DV

attend the self defense workshop(women & kids only) in association with
*universal power martial arts* on
*date:* 3rd march 2019 *time:* 10:30 am -12:30 pm
*venue:* mph *_what you will learn:_*
1.practical approach: trick to get out of the trapped situation
2.psychological approach: beat your opponent with your self confidence
3.self and social awareness in self defence
4.presence of mind
5.create a weapon out of anything *you are stronger than you think!*

text:
allegations of sexual harassment brings #metoo movement to nevada. : npr
#
melanie keener stands outside the storey county courthouse in virginia city, nev., where she now works in a largely undefined security job. after filing a sexual harassment complaint against sheriff gerald antinoro, keener was removed from her position as the sheriff's chief deputy. maggie starbard for npr hide caption toggle caption maggie starbard for npr melanie keener stands outside the storey county courthouse in virginia city, nev., where she now works in a largely undefined security job. after filing a sexual harassment complaint against sheriff gerald antinoro, keener was removed from her position as the sheriff's chief deputy. maggie starbard for npr in a small county in rural northern nevada, melanie keener was once the second-most powerful person in law enforcement. she was storey county's chief deputy, overseeing detentions, investigations and the patrol division. that ended in 2016 when she reported her boss, sheriff gerald antinoro, for sexual harassment. "coming forward has broke me," keener said. reporting her boss, she said, has ruined her nearly 20-year law enforcement career. she was removed from her position and relegated to an isolated desk in the storey county courthouse in virginia city. meanwhile, the man she accused, antinoro, remains the top law enforcement…

text:
please read ✨
.
never compromise your integrity for anyone. no matter what the cost.
.
what’s right is right and what’s wrong is wrong. and in the long run, more people get hurt with wrong doings.
.
i was confronted with one of the hardest decisions i ever made in my life at 17 years in the navy. i was told that if i said anything that i wouldn’t put on anchors and if i didn’t say anything they would make sure i didn’t put on anchors. so it was up to me to decide what was the right decision to make. and this was coming from my most trusted mentors.
.
you see, my best friend was being sexually harassed by our boss and we had exhausted our resources for help. our chain of command basically told her to “take it a little bit longer” because she needed his help.
.
i knew this man would not stop at her and continue to do this to others (and i was right). so i lodged a full fledged investigation.
.
i was first brow beaten into not going forward with the investigation. it was like something out of a movie. then i was remove from the command and relieved of all my duties as they told me they could no longer trust me. i received a promotable evaluation that cycle (and every other one after that). and this man still has a job.
.
i later found out that not one, but 3 others have lodged complaints against him and nothing has been done. it truly appalls me. i took it to ig and nothing!!
.
my point is, how do we expect people to speak out about sexual assault without repercussions? i spoke out, knowing this was a slight possibility but i want everyone to know what happens and to take heed and perhaps civil action vs. going through the naval channels. this man is a civilian, retired military and about to retire again. sitting pretty and enjoying his job.
.
this needs to stop!
.
share this story with as many people as you can. you may save someones life!!!
.
.

shesays london and brand genetics present: marketing & aspirational femininity. the #metoo movement has helped catalyse social change, challenging our understanding of gender roles and stereotypes. as a result, there is greater uncertainty today than ever before about what women want aspirational femininity to mean - with multiple different femininities emerging.⠀
⠀
as part of the wider celebration of international women’s day, brand genetics, a human-centred insight and innovation consultancy, will share findings from their new report into feminine identity, before hosting an industry-leading panel to discuss the question: what do women want from marketing in the #metoo era?⠀

text:
meet our sister - emma (@emma_clit)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
emma is a computer engineer and cartoonist focused on gender inequality. her comic strip 'you should have asked…', which condemns the so-called mental load women bear with regards to household chores, got worldwide appraisal.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
our journalist katha kloss (@kathakloss) said about emma: “she seems this girl next door, she says she’s not a good drawer but her comic strips on themes such as mental load have talked straight to the souls of thousands of women around the globe. that is her strength, she touches upon one of the last taboos, the ones deep down inside, of even emancipated women - striving for perfection between work, motherhood, family. yes, we can have it all now, can we? but at what prize? and how do we feel underneath? once you start talking, you’ll see that plenty of women share personal stories. thus emma is shamelessly freeing voices fostering female discourse and solidarity.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
photo by jef bonifacino
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#womenempowerment #sistersofeurope #metoo #feminism #europe #genderequality

pope francis’ former top financial advisor and the  vatican’s economy minister, cardinal george pell, has been found guilty of molesting choir boys more than 20 years ago, making him the highest-ranking roman catholic leader ever found guilty of sexual abuse. the 77-year-old, formally considered the third most powerful man in the vatican, was found guilty of forcing oral sex onto a 13-year-old boy after sunday mass in st. patrick’s cathedral in melbourne in 1996 when he was the city’s archbishop. he was also convicted of an assault in which he grabbed a boy’s genitals. the court heard testimony from one of the victims. the other victim died of a drug overdose in 2014, according to the bbc. sentencing proceedings are beginning on wednesday and are expected to last a few days. pell was found guilty in december, but a judge barred news outlets from publishing anything about the verdict out of concerns it would influence a jury in a second trial for an additional round of assault allegations. the suppression order was only lifted on tuesday after the second trial was canceled. pope francis expelled pell from his group of advisors in december. (📷: getty)
-

text:
i’m reaching the point where i’d like to start dating again but it is pretty scary.
i know rape victims often struggle with this. 
some of us lose our self-worth and make choices with no regard for our wellbeing. 
some of us shut down and avoid sex entirely.
some of us say “why not both?” 🙋🏼‍♀️
in my case this is exacerbated by identifying with the kink community. my alleged perpetrator disguised abuse and assault as kink when in reality they had no competence in how to practice safely. 
now, i don’t even trust a partner to get me coffee. but i’ve started swiping and plan to report my findings in my stories if you’re after some free entertainment. 
#raperecovery #rapesurvivor #kink #metoo #womenswave #ibelieveher #believesurvivors

.

.

..

seeing a victim-survivor speak out gives us hope. 
louder.

text:
(full article on www.doctorlarry.com, link in the bio)
jan 13 of this year, the razor company gillette released a commercial titled “we believe: the best men can be” which has proven to be quite controversial. in response, edgard watches ceo and founder ilan srulovicz, produced their own ad on masculinity. i’ve got both of them here on this page for you to watch. i’m curious what you think.

what is your gut reaction?
what message did you hear?

i’ll be honest, my intention with this post has evolved as i’ve dug into this issue. my initial reaction to the gillette was, “yes, spot on!” and to the egard take, “this, too, is powerful.” i wanted to use both videos to encourage a conversation on what it means to be your best, today’s gentleman–a strong, successful man of character, who treats everyone (especially women) with respect. *and does so, with style.

but, as the comments below attest, but many men absolutely hated the first ad, vowing to boycott gillette because of the it. sounds like we need to talk, so i’m going to start by listening. here’s some representative comments i have copied and pasted from the comments section of joe rogan’s podcast where he discussed it.

they’re trying to make parents suppress a young boys instinctual masculine traits and turn them into men that will cry at the end of watching titanic on the 5th viewing.

this is nothing more than radical feminist ideology wrapped in the once pure metoo movement. they’ve hijacked and mutated the metoo movement.

challenging men to be better is fine, but as soon as they use the #metoo movement as some sort of awakening for men. yep never buying another gillette product.﻿ how about we force all men to register as sex offenders? i’ve spent my entire life trying to respect others. and now i’m being accused of doing things i haven’t done simply because i’m a man.﻿ could you imagine a tampon commercial telling girls not to grow up to be materialistic, gossiping gold diggers.?﻿ can’t wait to see ‘the best a woman can be’ ad montage highlighting all the shitty things that women are capable of..

text:
tomorrow! 
tomorrow we scream! 
kyenvu. -by kemiyondo coutinho @kemi_yondo . "an independent young woman lives through the taunts of using public transport on a daily basis. as she struggles to find her footing in a patriarchal society that entitles men to women's bodies, she finds love in a bittersweet moment." she matters. -she matters @shematterstribe × suhayl omar @suhayllo × gathigia kinyua @gathigiakinyua . "in kenya, many rape victims have suffered embarrassment and fall under pressure and societal stigma to not share their stories. however, a current group of survivors are breaking these stereotypes and using their stories to pioneer change and reform. in this short documentary titled, 'she matters' we take a brief look into the lives and stories of survivors who were abused by those who they thought were closest to them. the subjects in the film are real-life victims of rape, who give their first hand accounts of their encounters, these stories enlighten men on the atrocities they have caused to women, while some may have messages of hope even after, some may not. this film is based on true-events in nairobi;kenya." this documentary was recently nominated for the gitw awards (girls impact the world) 
http://www.connecther.org/gitw/galleryview/id/1878

come thru' to pawa 254 @pawa254 from six pm, watch these films with us, join our discussion. we've had enough with the rape culture in this country. 
it must end. it will end. 
if you have any questions or suggestions, because those are important too, you can reach out to the organizers (us😅) @ngitomakena (me) 
and @suhayllo .

entry is just as free as our souls should be❤

text:
today i found myself doubting my worth. my ability to be like the others. to look and be a certain way. to fit a specific mould. and i surprised myself.
.
hello? are you fucking kidding me? waaaaaaa!
.
i took a long hard to look at myself in the mirror and thought... i have so much more to give than what i look like. why am i focusing on that shit instead of the things i am.
.
so i sat in front of the mirror and thought about everything i’ve been through... and all the things i’ve done. and realised... i’m actually ok. just the way i am.
.
i’m a #metoo thriver and a goal striver. my heart has an extra swoosh and my hair has extra smoosh. i survived an abusive relationship, that almost cost me my life, and i still have a smile on my face. i gave birth to three beautiful kids and, if i do say so myself, i’m the best goddamn mother around! i clean up puke, hold them with they are having a spinal tap in the emergency department and nurse them through fevers. i don’t just raise them, i raise them up. i navigated my way through divorce and came through stronger and wiser than ever. i can truly do anything! there is nothing you could throw at me that i am not already prepared for.
.
i’m sorry i doubted you and widdled your worth down to looks and aesthetics alone. what a foooooool!
.
this is me unfiltered. stripped bare. and i don’t need your approval... because i’m ok. i’m more than ok... i’m fucking golden.
.
we’ve got this.
.
i challenge you to do the same.
❤️🧡💛💚💙

text:
フラメンコは
毅然とした女性の
イメージなんだし、
せめて
「セクハラはいけません」
くらいは言って
ほしいですよね。

じゃないと存在として
薄っぺらいよね。
レイプすらも
怒れないなら
もう怒る事なんて
残ってなくない？

って事は、
ただ誰にでも
ペコペコするだけの
何されても
怒らない人たちが
足をダカダカ
やったりしてるわけ？

それなら
何にも考えてない
何の役にも立たない
存在感のない人達が
ただ目立ちたいだけの
内輪ノリの集まりって
事じゃん。

そのお手伝いを
僕が人生をかけて
しなきゃいけないの？
僕もその一員だ、
って事？

冗談じゃないよ。
人としての
意地くらい見せてよ。
人間の尊厳くらい
守ろうよ。

text:
the real life is happening around you while you’re staring at the screen of your smartphone 👽📱
the best thing about social networks is that they help you to stay tuned. but do we really need to be? scroll down news feed, constantly update fb and ig
i used to use social media as an entertaining platform but when i noticed that it takes too much time and distract from core activities, i stopped. 
it was hard at the beginning but i managed hehe. i wanna tell you some useful tips that will help you enjoy your real life. • notifications are the most distracting, turn them off • set an alarm for social media, i already use for ig and youtube • switch screen to black and white theme, i’ve learned that recently, but it’s powerful 
once my friend asked me: how is possible to be offline on a trip? and i told him: if something is going to happen, it will happen and i will get a call, at the same time nobody really gives a shit about your online presence, of course, except your fam 🧡
______________________

text:
▪️длинное платье является воплощением женственности, элегантности и стиля.

но чтобы женственность и элегантность не выглядело по-монашески, важно правильно подобрать по пропорциям верхнюю одежду согласно параметрам тела, а так же учесть стиль самого платья.

средний и небольшой рост.

верхняя одежда должна быть до талии, либо средней длины и всегда приталенной.

а в случае плаща или пальто при небольшом росте, пояс создаст верные пропорции.

итак, миниатюрные девушки присмотритесь к укороченным приталенным пальто, курткам из кожи и замши, меховым жилеткам.

высокий, модельный рост.
верхняя одежда будет зависеть от стиля платья.
кожаная куртка, куртка-парка, пальто, плащ или меховой жилет, либо вязаные и шерстяные вещи – свитера, кардиганы, пиджаки.

ансамбль длинное пальто с макси платьем, для девушки высокого роста будет идеальным.

а вам нравятся длинные платья в пол?
что из представленного в карусели одели бы?
-••-•••-••-•••-
▪️через преображение, влюбляю людей в самих себя▪️

"as parents, as aunts, uncles, brothers and sisters i think it is very important to have open dialogue within the family on issues such as personal safety, not associating abuse with the family’s honour, and allowing children to speak freely. if a child discloses abuse, support them in whatever way you can. believe a child if they talk about this – whether it is your child or not. don’t blame, ostracize or stigmatize them. people can familiarize themselves with the existing systems and laws. if your phone gets stolen most people know exactly where they need to go, but if a child is being abused most people don’t know whether to go to the police, a child welfare committee, an ngo, or to a hospital. and today – thanks to the internet – it is much easier to get this information." - kushi kushalappa, a social worker working with enfold trust, an ngo set up by physicians to support victims of child sexual abuse in india. #16days #hearmetoo #endviolence #childabuse #children #listentovictims #listentosurvivors #sexualassault #sexualabuse #metoo

text:
journalist priya ramani, whose allegation of sexual misconduct against m.j. akbar paved the way for the #metoo movement in india.

in the wake of ramani’s tweet, in which she identified him as the anonymous editor who featured in a magazine article she had written the previous year, multiple women came forward with accounts of alleged sexual harassment by him when he edited the asian age newspaper.

akbar was forced to resign as minister of state for external affairs last year as the allegations against him piled up, all dating back to his time as a newspaper editor.

priya ramani received bail by a delhi court this week in a criminal defamation case filed by m.j. akbar. 
the court had earlier summoned ramani after noting that the allegations made against akbar were “prima facie defamatory” and that he denied all the accusations made by her as “false and imaginary”. in a brief hearing that saw several journalists in attendance in solidarity with ramani, additional chief metropolitan magistrate samar vishal granted her bail on a bond of rs 10,000.

#feminism #feminist #metoo #metoomovement #indianfeminists #law #truth

text:
stories are powerful. last night, i gathered the courage to share mine on stage. i spoke about my experience of making peace with my math tuition teacher who molested me for two years when i was 11. i read out the letter i'd written to him and vulnerably shared my struggles.

my journey of healing has made me believe in the power of acceptance, forgiveness and love. anger, guilt and anxiety are corrosive. it's a never-ending process, but it's one that sets me free. it takes a lot of inner work and therapy, but i wouldn't do it any other way. i'm so grateful for all the support i've received, its because of it that i am where i am today.

thank you so much for giving me this opportunity, @kopalkhanna123. you're amazing 💜
.

the majority of ashkenazi jews are descended from prehistoric european women, according to study published today (october 8) in nature communications. while the jewish religion began in the near east, and the ashkenazi jews were believed to have origins in the early indigenous tribes of this region, new evidence from mitochondrial dna, which is passed on exclusively from mother to child, suggests that female ancestors of most modern ashkenazi jews converted to judaism in the north mediterranean around 2,000 years ago and later in west and central europe.

the new findings contradict previous assertions that ashkenazi mitochondrial lineages originated in the near east, or from mass conversions to judaism in the khazar kingdom, an empire in the north caucasus region between europe and asia lasting from the 7th century to the 11th century whose leaders adopted judaism. “we found that most of the maternal lineages don’t trace to the north caucasus, which would be a proxy for the khazarians, or to the near east, but most of them emanate from europe,” said coauthor martin richards, an archaeogeneticist at the university of huddersfield in the u.k.

text:
there are people who look guilty in court, and other people that just look annoyed that they're going to be late for their sex party with all the underage girls they've been trafficking and abusing because the ridiculously lenient plea bargain they're getting in lieu of prison time has a lot of paperwork involved...and that face, my friends, belongs to multimillionaire jeffrey epstein. 
he calls himself a financier, hedge fund manager, and science and research philanthropist, but i call him a pedophile, rapist, and sex trafficking piece of shit. epstein was under federal investigation 10 years ago for soliciting and sexually assaulting over 50 girls, most of whom were teenagers as young as 14 years old. being in the finance industry, he has quite the network of rich creeps that also partook in sex crimes with these girls including prince andrew, alan dershowitz, and you guessed it, donald j. trump. 
fast forward to an 11-month federal investigation, a 53-page federal indictment, substantial evidence, and victim statements with aligning details that should have been more than enough to send epstein to prison for life, but ended up being sealed and wiped away by alexander acosta; then federal prosecutor, now us secretary of labor. acosta concealed the details of epsteins crimes, shut down any further fbi investigation, and granted immunity to epstein, his accomplices, and any other possible co-conspirators in exchange for epstein pleading guilty to two prostitution charges in state court and serving an 18-month sentence, of which he only served 13, and was free to continue going to work, visiting his various vacation homes, and basically carrying on as usual. 
the worst part? this plea bargain was kept from the victims in the case. they were told that the investigation was on-going, and didn't find out about the plea deal until it was on the news. 
last week, district judge kenneth marra ruled that because acosta violated the crime victims' rights act, the plea deal could be thrown out and epstein and his co-conspirators would be subjected to new federal charges. so the pressure is on! get loud and make sure these fuckers pay for what they did!!🖕#metoosday

he calls himself a ficier, hedge fund manager, and science and research philanthropist, but i call him a pedophile, rapist, and sex trafficking piece of shit. epstein was under federal investigation 10 years ago for soliciting and sexually assaulting over 50 girls, most of whom were teenagers as young as 14 years old. being in the fice industry, he has quite the network of rich creeps that also partook in sex crimes with these girls including prince andrew, alan dershowitz, and you guessed it, donald j. trump. 
fast forward to an 11-month federal investigation, a 53-page federal indictment, substantial evidence, and victim statements with aligning details that should have been more than enough to send epstein to prison for life, but ended up being sealed and wiped away by alexander acosta; then federal prosecutor, now us secretary of labor. acosta concealed the details of epsteins crimes, shut down any further fbi investigation, and granted immunity to epstein, his accomplices, and any other possible co-conspirators in exchange for epstein pleading guilty to two prostitution charges in state court and serving an 18-month sentence, of which he only served 13, and was free to continue going to work, visiting his various vacation homes, and basically carrying on as usual. 
the worst part? this plea bargain was kept from the victims in the case. they were told that the investigation was on-going, and didn't find out about the plea deal until it was on the news. 
last week, district judge kenneth marra ruled that because acosta violated the crime victims' rights act, the plea deal could be thrown out and epstein and his co-conspirators would be subjected to new federal charges. so the pressure is on! get loud and make sure these fuckers pay for what they did!!🖕#metoosday

pope francis’ former top financial advisor and the  vatican’s economy minister, cardinal george pell, has been found guilty of molesting choir boys more than 20 years ago, making him the highest-ranking roman catholic leader ever found guilty of sexual abuse. the 77-year-old, formally considered the third most powerful man in the vatican, was found guilty of forcing oral sex onto a 13-year-old boy after sunday mass in st. patrick’s cathedral in melbourne in 1996 when he was the city’s archbishop. he was also convicted of an assault in which he grabbed a boy’s genitals. the court heard testimony from one of the victims. the other victim died of a drug overdose in 2014, according to the bbc. sentencing proceedings are beginning on wednesday and are expected to last a few days. pell was found guilty in december, but a judge barred news outlets from publishing anything about the verdict out of concerns it would influence a jury in a second trial for an additional round of assault allegations. the suppression order was only lifted on tuesday after the second trial was canceled. pope francis expelled pell from his group of advisors in december. (📷: getty)
-

text:
one day long ago a little girl sat on a cold bench huddling a smaller boy. the police lights flooded her eyes but even more so difficult questions overflowed her mind. there were no answers- she vowed she wouldn’t ever let this happen again. 5 years later the girl was brought back to that empty dark place in her mind as she sat staring blankly into the snow, confused and hurt in ways she didn’t really understand but she told herself one day she would never let another person have this grip on her mind. 6 years following that she holds her son while quietly crying to herself, blaming herself for her gullible tendencies- asking how she could let this happen again- but it’s different, it’s always different. and no matter how many times she finds that dark distant place in her mind, she comes back. because she makes plans, goals, and she rises. i don’t know what the future holds, the only apology i have left is to the little girl. the one that didn’t know, but tried- but with the knowledge that every time she falls, she rises. every hero is born from this place- and yet another promise is made. no one will ever take my voice again. 
the benefit of being drug through hell, by someone else,  is this- when you finally find your footing you will always be their greatest nightmare- you survived. #thoughts #domesticviolence #domesticabuse #survivor #metoo #iampowerful #stronger #smarter #myvoice #findingstrength #womensupportingwomen #livingagain #truth #iamme #nomore #real #woahthatsdeep

text:
16 - h e r  s t o r y

a graphic essay on the #metoo movement in india. 
this essay addresses sexual harassment at the workplace in india, and how many have reacted to it. 
it is a deeper look at the #metoo movement in india, for which i’ve collaborated with the polis project ( @thepolisproject ). if you think this message is important, relevant or have faced similar questions in discussions about the movement, please consider sharing this! 
the entire essay is available on the polis project’s website, and is linked in my bio. it’s best viewed on a larger screen, so pleaseee do me and your eyesight a favour and check it out on the website!

text:
the women’s conference will explore some of the realities faced by women, with a focus
on the struggles and challenges faced by women from three main communities in malaysia: the
local, refugee and migrant communities. through this conference, we aspire to find a common ground for women to feel safe and to stand united in solidarity with each other. by highlighting many of the struggles faced by women, the aim is to strengthen the sense of community among women currently in malaysia.

date: 2nd march 2019, saturday
time: 10.30 am to 4.30 pm
venue: level 1, ruang by think city,
2, jalan hang kasturi, kuala lumpur

see you ladies there! 
#unitedinstruggle #womenempowerment #timeisnow #metoo #beyondborders #mewro #tenaganita #tanma #refugees #womenup #women #debrajeannepoh #debless #blessed

text: the gym environment has transformed into a place where women no longer feel safe while working out. unfortunately, the gym can be a place where women are approached, watched, and sometimes photographed by (usually) men. it is saddening and upsetting that women attend the gym to feel better about themselves to only receive harassment. some women feel the need to wear longer tops to cover their bums, purposely look “uglier” at the gym to reduce the amount of male attraction, or attend the gym at times where it is not busy. judith levine’s article totaled “beyond #metoo” touched in the #metoo movement that has spread across the nation. i found it extremely interesting that the hashtag has spread accords the fitness industry and enabled women to speak up of sexual harassment that happens at the gym.

text:
the incredibly strong and inspiring mita naidu brings her passion to one of our panels next week for this year's women's awareness week #iwd2019 in vancouver. .
.
after an early career in academia, and non profit leadership- i am now deeply embedded in communications, diversity and equity strategy, fundraising, community empowerment, and advocacy. my passions have always been entangled in the arts, sports, education, notions of voice, diaspora, south asian intersectional feminism and anti-oppression work. trained in bharat natyam and ballet. i performed at the winter olympics in 2010, and taught dance for many years. now, those aspirations have been channeled into community via directorship on several prominent boards including: the vancouver international jazz festival/coastal jazz festival; the vancouver international children’s festival; and deltassist. previous board experiences include the city-appointed cultural communities advisory committee; the vancouver asian heritage month society; the indian summer festival; and diwali celebration society. published in academic journals, as well as mainstream media publications- my voice and perspectives are sought by those looking for insight into canadian social and educational issues. i am often asked to speak in classrooms and formal panels about social justice, diversity, intersectionality and diasporic issues. i am the recipient of two bc arts council grants, and was named one of “12 remarkable women in vancouver” by the city of vancouver and the vancouver parks board in 2012.
born in kolkata, india, i grew up in canada; and keep my life balanced through community work, volunteerism, sports, the arts and youth movements. as a single mother of two remarkable children (12 & 16) i also care for my mother and reside in delta.
.
. 
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10)
https://iwd2019vancouver.eventbrite.ca or the link in @minibarcanada’s profile.

text:
it always feels like she's one of the founders of vancouver's wine industry - honoured to welcome the legendary dj kearney to one of our panels next week for this year's women's awareness week #iwd2019 in vancouver. .
.
dj kearney’s decades in the wine industry have embraced teaching, wine writing and wine criticism. she has trained over a thousand sommelier candidates throughout north america for the international sommelier guild, in a decade of non-stop travel to cities like seattle, portland, las vegas, los angeles, denver, san diego and many more. dj has consulted for many global wine marketing bodies — including wines of chile, wines of south africa, wines of california, wines of germany, wines of australia, jura wines, sopexa, and wines of argentina — while leading educational master-classes for these entities around north america.
she has frequently appeared on television and radio and moderates, presents and judges at wine festivals and competitions around the globe. having traveled to most major wine regions of the world, dj brings a truly global perspective to her work. she holds a b.a., the wset diploma, and the isg sommelier certification, and has spent four years in the master of wine program. she has been the drink editor for vancouver magazine, critic/contributor for winealign, and wine director for http://newdistrict.ca. 
dj is a seasoned wine judge and has started programs developing and mentoring the next generation of judges in canada.  throughout the year, she can be found teaching the wine and spirit education trust professional wine classes at the pacific institute of culinary arts, as well as the newly launched caps sommelier diploma program. she is vice-president of the canadian association of professional sommeliers, bc chapter, and a member of les dames d’escoffier.
.
. 
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10)

text:
the incredibly strong and inspiring mita naidu brings her passion to one of our panels next week for this year's women's awareness week #iwd2019 in vancouver. .
.
after an early career in academia, and non profit leadership- i am now deeply embedded in communications, diversity and equity strategy, fundraising, community empowerment, and advocacy. my passions have always been entangled in the arts, sports, education, notions of voice, diaspora, south asian intersectional feminism and anti-oppression work. trained in bharat natyam and ballet. i performed at the winter olympics in 2010, and taught dance for many years. now, those aspirations have been channeled into community via directorship on several prominent boards including: the vancouver international jazz festival/coastal jazz festival; the vancouver international children’s festival; and deltassist. previous board experiences include the city-appointed cultural communities advisory committee; the vancouver asian heritage month society; the indian summer festival; and diwali celebration society. published in academic journals, as well as mainstream media publications- my voice and perspectives are sought by those looking for insight into canadian social and educational issues. i am often asked to speak in classrooms and formal panels about social justice, diversity, intersectionality and diasporic issues. i am the recipient of two bc arts council grants, and was named one of “12 remarkable women in vancouver” by the city of vancouver and the vancouver parks board in 2012.
born in kolkata, india, i grew up in canada; and keep my life balanced through community work, volunteerism, sports, the arts and youth movements. as a single mother of two remarkable children (12 & 16) i also care for my mother and reside in delta.
.
. 
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10)

text:
kitchen table's jennifer rossi joins the panel for this year's women's awareness week for #iwd2019 in vancouver. we are truly excited!
.
.
for jennifer rossi, the term ‘kitchen table’ represents more than simply the name of the local restaurant group she has helped steer for the past decade — it also speaks to the authentic and familial approach she takes toward work, life and community.

born and raised in vancouver, jennifer received an early education in the hospitality industry by working her way up the rungs of her grandfather’s restaurant and food-services company with roles as a line cook, host, server, bartender and manager. after two years in various front-of-house positions with cactus restaurants ltd., she added the title of owner to her resume when she co-founded kitchen table and opened the comfort-food-and-cocktail hotspot pourhouse in vancouver’s historic gastown district in 2009.

two years later, kitchen table bolstered its portfolio by setting up shop with the northern italian-focused pizzeria farina and casual italian eatery ask for luigi in 2014, which went on to win restaurant of the year, best new restaurant, best casual and best italian at the 2015 vancouver magazine restaurant awards. in 2017 the group opened st. lawrence, which won best restaurant and best new restaurant at the 2018 vancouver magazine restaurant awards and no. 4 on enroute’s list of canada’s best new restaurants.

no matter how significant the strides she continues to make with kitchen table, jennifer never forgets the core principles that were instilled in her during her formative days in the industry: putting personal and professional integrity first, treating colleagues and coworkers as you would family and fully embracing the notion that the fondest memories are made at the kitchen table.
.
. 
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10)

text:
the strippers in los angeles are hot under the collar about new state laws that changed the nature of their business relationship with club owners. what was billed as a way to ensure fair pay for the dancers has wound up costing them money and done nothing to alleviate other complaints about issues they run into while working. now they’re going on strike because they want to see some improvements and they’re getting some support from representatives of the #metoo movement. a group of adult dancers says they aren’t getting a fair shake at los angeles strip clubs, and it’s in part because of a california court ruling.
the group calls themselves “soldiers of pole” and they’re picketing outside the crazy girls club in hollywood where they’re demanding, among other things, fair wages. they say a state court ruling changed their status from independent contractors to actual employees.the dancers say now that clubs have to pay the women an hourly wage, management has been keeping a much larger chunk of their tips. they also claim that some clubs have been stealing their wages and charging dancers new fees ever since the new ruling, and they want it to stop.

text:
hey sis, 
how you feeling? 
i know its still early in the day but there’s so much to learn, explore and experience so why not jump right into it? 
on tuesday’s we talk about “it” 
whatever it may be, sexual abuse, trauma, healing... this is our platform to heal and express to/with each other. 
with that being said... i will be the first to go. 
btw my story may be triggering as it is hard for me to even find the words to express. i’ll begin with part 1
and be as honest as i can.
.
.
.
.
call them by their name 
it all happened in cincinnati, ohio 
my home town. 
he was my “uncle” or atleast that’s who he pretend to be. 
adrian. adrian lundy. 
yeah that’s his name. 
that’s the man who molested me when i was only 6 years old. .
.
.
.
.
blackout 
because of the traumatic experience i have blacked out most of what happened. 
i remember a few things like me telling him “no”
him trying to have me mock pornography and perform sexual acts on him. 
it wasn’t just me neither. 
he was my mother’s, best friend boyfriend whom my two “cousins” lived with. 
i remember wanting to tell soooo bad but at such a young age i was already carrying the weight of others. 
up until i was about 12 and i got fed up. 
i told my biological cousin, who told her mom, who told my mom, and my mom called the police 
just as any mother should do. .
.
.
.
no evidence, no prosecutions. 
that’s how the system is. because i couldn’t remember everything, because i was afraid, because i spoke up alone. 
the police didn’t do anything. 
even with them knowing that he made us all watch porno. 
they didn’t do anything. 
and i had to suffer... i mean we have suffered all this long and my abuser is still free.
.
.
.
.
healing, i am worthy. 
although this is not the only sexual abuse i have experienced in my young 26 years
it is the first that molded me into a victim. 
however, after being so fed up and defined by what had happened to me i eventually looked in my mirror and recognized who i am. 
i am no man’s sex slave
i am no man’s toy 
i am not a victim 
but a survivor 
and had i not been through what i’ve gone through... would i be able to heal the world the way i desire to? .
.
.
.
finished in commen

text:
i am living proof that you are not just a sum of your experiences. we don't have control over the past. but we have control over what we choose in the present. you can choose to continue to suffer. you can choose to ignore your needs & remain complacent, not caring about what happens to you or your life, mind, & body. you can choose to do what i and many other survivors have done: get up. take care of yourself. start small. anywhere is better than nowhere, anything is better than what you're doing to yourself. i know it isn't easy. it wasn't easy for me either, it's not supposed to be. but nobody knows you better than you know yourself. look at what you've been through, look at how you've survived. you're still here, wretched but so beautifully alive. i believe in you. i believe in your destiny & journey. i'm here to tell you, i did it. i found myself again. so many of us have. you have support in an entire community of us, standing in the millions. i promise, from the bottom of my heart, you will be okay. your dreams can come true. you just have to believe you are capable of healing, that you are worth it. you just have to choose yourself, because you deserve to. ✨

text:
the world had told them to feel shame, to cover up, to hide. 
as the camera clicked, the women sighed. they were tired. tired of covering, tired of hiding. tired of fighting for the right to be seen. 
the sun rose behind and the waves whipped their fury. cloaks were thrown off, vulnerability wavered and the mothers roared. 
sagging breasts. loose skin. stretch marks and dimples. 
naked shame no more. 
read the full blog, link in bio.

.
.

text:
kayla here. in this day and age it saddens me that i feel so incredibly fortunate to not only work alongside talented men but feel safe and respected while doing so.
today i directed a short film on domestic violence that raises questions surrounding the depiction of women’s bodies in film and how audiences comfort level change when the point of nudity isn’t for the male gaze.
having been sexually harassed (to put it mildly) on film sets in the past the idea of performing triggering stunt work half naked was terrifying but the day ended up being overwhelmingly hopeful knowing that i am surrounded by men i consider allies. 
thankyou @rstunts902 @kyledouglasforbes @jeff_babineau

text:
when skydance media chief executive #davidellison announced this year that he was hiring #johnlasseter to head skydance animation, many in and outside the company were shocked and deeply unhappy. only months earlier, lasseter had ended his relationship with pixar — where he had worked since the early ’80s — and parent company disney after multiple allegations of inappropriate behavior and the creation of a frat house-like work environment. lasseter had admitted to inappropriate hugging and “other missteps.” after announcing the hire, ellison sent a long email to staff, noting that lasseter was contractually obligated to behave professionally, and convened a series of town halls in which lasseter apologized for past behavior and asked to be given the chance to prove himself to his new staff. meanwhile, mireille soria, president of paramount pictures animation, with which skydance has a distribution deal, took the highly unusual step of meeting with female employees to tell them that they could decline to work with lasseter.

john lasseter’s return proves that hollywood still does not understand the damage he did

but it was #emmathompson, the politically outspoken newly anointed dame commander of the british empirewho made the first real definitive statement on lasseter, and one of the most significant decisions in post-#metoo hollywood.

in mid-february, it was reported that the two-time oscar winner had pulled out of skydance’s highly touted animation feature “luck,” citing her concerns about lasseter’s hiring. according to her representatives, from the moment the hire was announced, thompson began conversations about extricating herself from the project; she officially withdrew jan. 20.

in a letter she sent to #skydance management three days later, she acknowledged the complications caused by a star withdrawing from a project, including the effect her decision would have on the director, the rest of the cast and the crew. but in the end, she wrote, the questions raised by the lasseter hire made it impossible for her to remain in the film.

thompson declined to comment on her decision, but she made the letter available to @latimes
name: feminin in society

text:
i try not to post the same images on my business and personal social media but i am making an exception this one time .
in this day and age it saddens me that i feel so incredibly fortunate to not only work alongside talented men but feel safe and respected while doing so.
today i directed a short film on domestic violence that raises questions surrounding the depiction of women’s bodies in film and how audiences comfort level change when the point of nudity isn’t for the male gaze.
having been sexually harassed (to put it mildly) on film sets in the past the idea of performing triggering stunt work half naked was terrifying but the day ended up being overwhelmingly hopeful knowing that it is possible to have men you consider allies. 
beautiful stills photography by @kyledouglasforbes

text:
nicole powell, dap’s outreach education specialist, visits high schools, middle schools, colleges and community organizations across delaware county, providing preventative education on domestic violence and available services. 
when working with teenage populations, creativity is key.  one of the ways nicole engages students is through in their shoes: teens and dating violence, a game that gives teenagers the opportunity to play a character experiencing real life situations such as pregnancy, stalking, homophobia and sexting. through the facilitation, players make choices about their interactions with dating partners, family members, counselors, friends and police.  by utilizing a creative simulation with a diverse view on unhealthy relationships, nicole facilitates productive conversations and offers preventative education to teenagers for maintaining healthy relationships. 
are you interested in having dap’s outreach education specialist speak at your school, college, business or community organization provide preventative education on domestic violence and available resources for victims? call dap’s main office at 610-565-6272 for more information. 
#teendvmonth #loveisrespect #breakthecycle #timeisup #loveshouldalwaysbesafe #metoo #startheconversaton #dontjustwatch #dapdv2019 #delawarecountypa #mediapa #loveisnotabuse

text:
i asked my 4 y/o for a hug and he said no. 
me: okay. no problem.
my son: does it make you sad when i don’t hug you?
me: what you do with your body is your choice and you don’t have to hug when you don’t want to. and you shouldn’t get upset if you want to hug someone and that someone doesn’t want a hug. i will never be upset with you for knowing what you want and what you don’t want.
my son: thank you. 
then, he hugged me.

and that’s how easy it is to teach consent. one quick conversation at a time. #teachconsent #metoo #timesup

text:
#as you know, i have pulled out of the production of “luck” l to be directed by the very wonderful alessandro carloni. it feels very odd to me that you and your company would consider hiring someone with mr. lasseter’s pattern of misconduct given the present climate in which people with the kind of power that you have can reasonably be expected to step up to the plate.

i realise that the situation — involving as it does many human beings — is complicated. however these are the questions i would like to ask:

if a man has been touching women inappropriately for decades, why would a woman want to work for him if the only reason he’s not touching them inappropriately now is that it says in his contract that he must behave “professionally”? if a man has made women at his companies feel undervalued and disrespected for decades, why should the women at his new company think that any respect he shows them is anything other than an act that he’s required to perform by his coach, his therapist and his employment agreement? the message seems to be, “i am learning to feel respect for women so please be patient while i work on it. it’s not easy.” much has been said about giving john lasseter a “second chance.” but he is presumably being paid millions of dollars to receive that second chance. how much money are the employees at skydance being paid to give him that second chance?

if john lasseter started his own company, then every employee would have been given the opportunity to choose whether or not to give him a second chance. but any skydance employees who don't want to give him a second chance have to stay and be uncomfortable or lose their jobs. shouldn’t it be john lasseter who has to lose his job if the employees don’t want to give him a second chance?
skydance has revealed that no women received settlements from pixar or disney as a result of being harassed by #johnlasseter. but given all the abuse that’s been heaped on women who have come forward to make accusations against powerful men, do we really think that no settlements means that there was no harassment or no hostile work environment? (...)"
@emmathompson

#metoo #activism  #sexualharassment #sexualassault

the best collections from new york fashion week fall 2019

over the past few years, new york fashion week has been charged with a sense of purpose. it reflected the political and social climate immediately, commenting on the 2016 presidential election, the #metoo and times up movements and was the standard-bearer of size and race inclusivity—something that is still sorely lacking in other fashion capitals. these headline-making attributes were celebrated and received tremendous media coverage.

but for the fall 2019 season, little attention was given to these initiatives. and that’s perhaps a good thing.
