text:
i miss my stepdaughter’s energy. i miss her smile. her laugh. helping her with her hair, waxing her legs. cheering for her to succeed. washing her clothes. telling her to help with dishes. driving her to her friends. making her food lots of yummy food. getting her to drink my kombucha worrying about her gut health. helping her vocalize her dreams and write them down to achieve them. listening to her giggle with her little sister. hearing her cuddle with her cat. having to duck and cover as she throws her legs around. being there every step of the way with school and dance. i miss everything about her. her heart of gold i miss the most. i send her love and hold onto what everyone says. that it won’t always be like this. that when she gets older she will see things differently. never in a million years did i think at the end of all that has happened to us that it will be she and i having to repair, that we are the most broken apart. but her mother wanted to destroy me for a misconception that i have destroyed her daughter. the next best thing would be destroying my relationship with her daughter which she has done. but love doesn’t die. i loved her and i know she loved me too ♥️ -
-
-
-

text:
our food tastes better when infused with social justice ingredients. the amazing speakers and presenters at the moroccan soup bar conversation salon” the promise of the me too movement: the intersectional experience “ prof gillian triggs, lidia thorpe, samah sabawi, sarah saleh, aseel tayah. the origins of the me too movement began with african american women calling out abuses, violations and coercions of women who lived in the intersections between misogyny and racism. notable in our discussion is the need to recognise our privileges & form coalitions with indigenous women who are calling for treaty. the experience of violence for indigenous women intersects with the experience of indigenous communities still struggling for legitimacy and treaty in a system built on their violation and abuse. the importance of this message today in the face of continuing hostilities towards indigenous women and women of colour: we must recognise, a movement needs to reach across the social divide and strengthen its vision if it is to truly sustain and liberate all women. 
intersectional experience requires that we recognise ourselves in the struggles of the other and within an overarching culture of human rights. 
a call to building a movement of coalitions which connects with all  forms of resistance from the arts to politics, community to hospitality this was the beginning of many. thank you to a community with a growing hunger for a better world. stay tuned for more. #vegetarian #community #feminism #intersectionalfeminism #whatsonmelbourne #moroccan #diversity #metoo #socialjustice

text:
this is what i do in the off-season 🤷🏼‍♀️ on a snowy, cold, emotional night i got together with a friend and we made some art! it was good to get out of my head for a couple hours. 
inside i was falling apart. on the outside i’m proud of how all of my hard work in the past year has paid off. i’m not shy to get in front of the camera, i do feel beautiful. 
i just wish the way i felt on the outside could match the inside. i wish i could feel beautiful on the inside more of the time. living with mental illness is exhausting. it’s frustrating. it’s discouraging. 
it can also be empowering, but i don’t have this feeling very often. 
empowering because despite everything going on in my head—i manage to raise three beautiful girls, work as a nurse, have amazing friends and family, and challenge my body by training for running events and triathlons. 
thanks @dannygrause for being one of the good friends in my life and i look forward to making all sorts of art with you in the future! .
.

.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
hhs docs show thousands of alleged incidents of sexual abuse against unaccompanied minors in custody

the department of health and human services received more than 4,500 complaints of sexual abuse against unaccompanied minors from 2014-2018, according to internal agency documents released tuesday by florida democratic rep. ted deutch.

in addition,1,303 complaints were reported to the justice department during that same time frame, according to the documents.

deutch addressed the documents during a high-profile house hearing tuesday on the trump administration's "zero tolerance" policy that resulted in thousands of immigrant children being separated from their parents.

he said that the documents "demonstrate over the past three years, there have been 154 staff on unaccompanied minor, let me repeat that, staff on unaccompanied minor allegations of sexual assault." "this works out on average to one sexual assault by hhs staff on unaccompanied minor per week," he added.
axios first reported the documents. "i am deeply concerned with documents that have been turned over by hhs that record a high number of sexual assaults on unaccompanied children in the custody of the office of refugee and resettlement," deutch said. "together, these documents detail an environment of systemic sexual assaults by staff on unaccompanied children." hhs spokesperson caitlin oakley addressed the reports in a statement, saying minors' safety is a "top concern," and noted that there are "rigorous standards" in place for employees, which include mandatory background checks. "these are vulnerable children in difficult circumstances, and orr fully understands its responsibility to ensure that each child is treated with the utmost care. when any allegations of abuse, sexual abuse, or neglect are made, they are taken seriously and orr acts swiftly to investigate and respond," oakley said.

at the hearing tuesday, hhs' us public health service commissioned corps commander, jonathan white, defended his agency against accusations of sexual abuse when asked by rep. tom

to learn more visit legalactionnews.com

always an emotional moment when you open up that print proof for the first time. 😍🤩💗💓💓💓 so in love with this second book of ours, puritan u by kristin garth coming next month in march! thanks to everyone who has ordered so far. please consider supporting the author and her tale of strength & bravery, her story of survival and resilience by preordering today! (rhythmnbone.com/puritan-u).
———
kristin garth is a pushcart & best of the net nominated sonnet stalker.  her poetry has stalked magazines like @glasspoetrypress, @yespoetry, @five2onemag, anti-heroin chic, former cactus, @occulumjournal , @lunalunamag, & many more.  she has four chapbooks pink plastic house and good girl games (@maverickduckpress), pensacola girls (@boneandinkpress, sept 2018) and shakespeare for sociopaths (hedgehog poetry press). she has another forthcoming, puritan u (rhythm & bones press march 2019). her full length, candy cigarette, is forthcoming april 2019 (the hedgehog poetry press). she has a collaborative full length a victorian dollhousing ceremony forthcoming (rhythm & bones press) in june 2019.  follow her on twitter: (@ lolaandjolie), and her website (kristingarth.com).
———

'a feminilidade não se opõe ao feminismo. feminismo é antes de tudo sobre liberdade'
.
. ・・・
"vibrar a  essência da feminilidade sagrada é escutar e se afinar ao som que foi abafado em nosso ser. celebrar este encontro, não está em seguir um movimento de semelhança superficial e condicional. o movimento é da alma, negativando qualquer regra imposta por gênero e dogmas preestabelecidos, é respirar em sua plenitude natural, selvagem e instintiva, aí mesmo onde você se encontra... seja como for, e com o dom e a força natural...
é um caminho interior de brilho e contentamento com sua plena existência. a dança do seu som original, alma que desenvolve satisfeita e coerente, flutuando na esfera do amor.
temos todas muito em comum, mas somos expressões únicas, tanto como as estrelas que possuem intensidade e luminosidade distintas e magnitude própria.
ouvidos abertos, coração desperto e poder suficiente de ser quem você realmente é." texto de clau sbano

text:
this account was tagged in this post (2nd pic), and i can’t help but share to lift my voice and other voices of women who have been harassed, abused, bullied, or discriminated against in the workplace.
*
i am the victim (or survivor) of violence in the workplace. i am also a victim of harassment and bullying by male executives. unfortunately, the first occurrence of abuse happened to me a few weeks shy of the #metoo movement. my abuser is an executive at one of the largest companies in the country that promotes a culture of diversity and inclusion. and yet he still walks the halls without consequence and continues to intimidate me in the office. because i am a single woman and need that job, and also out of fear of retaliation, his abuse was only reported once.
*
the abuse i suffered was not physical. and, sadly, in mainstream society, people don’t understand that abuse isn’t just physical—it can also be psychological, emotional, and financial, among many other forms. i have chosen to be a voice of hope and change so that one day people will know that abuse takes many forms. abuse is not just physical. psychological abuse is domestic violence, and it should not occur in the workplace period. unfortunately, this is the world we live in—a world where abusers/harassers get promoted and patted on the backs by their cohorts as mine has. i can only hope and fight for change and support other victims of domestic violence and harassment. i hope that one day in telling my story i will be able to help someone else. i also hope that one day in telling my story people will be baffled and unable to believe that’s how the world once was.
*
i am a fighter, and i’m fighting for change.
*
#abuseisntjustphysical #enddomesticviolence #endharrassment #metoo #ihearyou #ibelieveyou #isupportyou #youarenotalone
*
#womeninthelaw #womeninlaw #womenlawyerssupportingwomenlawyers #wlswl

text:
i don't say this only to share my story. i'm saying this to let others know that they are not alone.
so listen. those who force someone to fuck, beg them till they say yes, violating personal boundaries are all examples of sexual assault. it is anything sexual that was not consented to. to those who need to hear it, it never was and never will be your fault, you are strong, you are loved and you are so brave for making it through each day.
we are constantly being told to do things that could prevent sexual assault, how about people just don't do it? please educate yourself on consent, what rape/sexual assault is and i urge anyone dealing with the trauma of sexual assault to reach out for help. #metoo

you are always welcome to come talk to me if you ever need someone to talk to. i am here for you.

text:
this past sunday, february 24th, “period. end of sentence” took home the award for best short documentary at the 91st #academyawards. this film demonstrates the problem that is #periodpoverty and how it can affect the education of girls, focusing in india. however, once sanitary pad machines were installed, women in a village outside of delhi learned to produce their own, biodegradable pads. no woman should have to be shamed for menstruation, nor face repercussions from it. no girl should have to risk their education and be hindered from reaching their potential. it is time for a change, for a better future. •
•

are you experiencing domestic violence?
do you know of someone who is experiencing abuse and may need help and support?
the freephone 24 hour national domestic violence helpline, run in partnership between women's aid and refuge, is a national service for women experiencing domestic violence, their family, friends, colleagues and others calling on their behalf.

the helpline can give support, help and information over the telephone, wherever the caller might be in the country. the helpline is staffed 24 hours a day by fully trained female helpline support workers and volunteers. all calls are completely confidential. translation facilities for callers whose first language is not english, and a service for callers who are deaf or hard of hearing are available

text: “bedstuy brooklyn bather” - saturday night painting in progress. this bathroom in bedstuy is so small, that i sometimes put the painting in the hallway and work from my position seated on the toilet. she has become diana in my mind and i am actaeon. i even bought her a pair of diana’s hunter moon earrings to wear while she sits. a more important and substantial aspect of the making of this painting has to do with all of the things we talk about and a great and building friendship. we started this painting in 2015. we’ve had a lot to talk about. i’ll miss our intimate saturday night bathroom hangouts when this one is finished. #blacklivesmatter #metoo #dianaandactaeon #bathers

text:
women shouldn’t feel unsafe walking home from work, or laying in the sun in a brisbane park such as my story.  this is such a big issue. since my encounter i have talked to so many of my friends and family and all but some have similar stories, some of which made me cry. to think i was one of the lucky ones, for the simple fact he didn’t catch me. #metoomovement #metoo 
my soft strands wrapped around your fingertips, you lower those cool blue eyes and i feel your gaze linger on what you want. i am a dear in your headlights, unable to move and confused as to the situation i’m in.. i welcomed this though, didn’t i?, ask for it in a way?. you asked if you could sit and i reluctantly obliged, silly girl. i am now running, running as fast as i can every thud like thunder echoing in my ears. turning around i see only those blue eyes, never halting their assault. i will never be the same because of those cold blue eyes

text: mindfulness the practice of paying attention and staying present in the moment—has increasingly gained popularity in recent years. perhaps this is because the more our world is consumed by technology, the harder it seems to be mindful. instead of spending even a second alone, staying present with our thoughts, we reflexively turn to our cellphones for entertainment, comfort, or distraction. many of us are on our phones at work, in the bathroom, and even during sex—moments that in the past might have been spent unintentionally being mindful. so how do reclaim those mindful moments and again learn how to stay present, aware, and accepting of those moments? https://youwillbearwitness.com/2019/02/26/what-is-mindfulness-and-how-to-be-more-mindful/ #youwillbearwitness #emdr #erinfado #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #metoo #dissociativeidentitydisorder #trauma #doitfordolly  #therapydog

text:
https://amzn.to/2hyfwo0 ❤️ „abgründe“ und „obsession“ aus der serie „flüsternde schatten“ von melia rosta

leserstimmen: "abgründe" flüsternde schatten 1

der erste band von melia rostas neuer biographischer reihe ‚flüsternde schatten‘ verlangt dem leser gleich alles ab. denn der abstieg der jungen nina in die zwangsprostitution ist keine überzogene fantasie, sondern nackte realität – eine realität, die der heutigen gesellschaft vollkommen fremd erscheint, für tausende von frauen in den deutschen großstädten aber allzu realer alltag ist.

dieses buch bietet einblicke in eine szene, die den meisten lesern vollkommen fremd erscheint, und öffnet eine welt, von der man sonst nur einen schwachen schatten erlebt. ********************************************* "obsession" flüsternde schatten 2

scheint es auf den ersten blick so, als habe die junge prostituierte nina in ihrem neuen freund nico endlich einen soliden partner gefunden, so kehren sich die rollen schnell um. schon bald treibt sich nico selbst in die finanzielle abhängigkeit; er betrügt nina, er prügelt sie, wenn sie nicht genug geld bringt – kurz, er wird zu ihrem neuen zuhälter.

diese wahre geschichte zeigt auf allzu reale art, wie die rotlicht-szene ihre bewohnner an sich kettet, wie geld korrumpiert und wie selbst der netteste kerl von nebenan sich von dem goldenen glanz eines feuerzeugs blenden lassen kann.

text:
at age 13, i was questioning if i miscarrying my fathers child. (i didn't know what happened to my body.
at age 14, i stood before a judge and lied to protect my family. 
at age 15, i was trapped for almost 4 years. 
and then in my early 20s...well, i took the road less traveled. 
no matter what happened, no matter what i did or didn't do,  jesus never stopped pursuing me. he didn't run away from my messy life. in fact, he stepped right into it and stayed. jesus gave up his life so that i could live. he forgave me. so i forgive others. those forgiven much, love much. those who have needed to be forgiven much, understand this well. there is nothing that can separate us from the love of god. there is no sin that is too big that he won't forgive. god loved us so much, he gave up his only son. god is love. 
love requires us to let others know, we are not alone. and you my friends are not alone. whatever it is you face, if you're struggling with sin or just feel like something in your life is missing. jesus is the answer. i can't wait to see him face to face. :)
#speak #speakyoursilence #thestitch #sexualabuse #mylifepointstojesus #metoo #survivor #overcameit #overcame #zigzag

text:
i am so excited about this giveaway!

i’ve teamed up with the awesome folks over at @the_librarycard card to give someone one of their adorable totes filled with goodies.

i really want my little corner of the internet to be a place that helps motivate you to take this life and turn it into something amazing! god didn’t send us here to just endure this life, he sent us here to create something wonderful out of it.

from now on, my feed will be broken down into the three categories i focus on to create the life i want: mental, spiritual & physical (and food, of course 😉, because i just love food) and you can find posts related to each by their associated hashtags. #asoulsurvivormental, #asoulsurvivorspiritual, #asoulsurvivorphysical.

kicking off these hashtags with a giveaway for each one! 🙌🏻🙌🏻 today’s will center around mental health.

giveaway closed. congratulations @bayleebrewer23 send me a dm to claim your prize!

i really want my little corner of the internet to be a place that helps motivate you to take this life and turn it into something amazing! god didn’t send us here to just endure this life, he sent us here to create something wonderful out of it.

from now on, my feed will be broken down into the three categories i focus on to create the life i want: mental, spiritual & physical (and food, of course 😉, because i just love food) and you can find posts related to each by their associated hashtags. #asoulsurvivormental, #asoulsurvivorspiritual, #asoulsurvivorphysical.

kicking off these hashtags with a giveaway for each one! 🙌🏻🙌🏻 today’s will center around mental health.

giveaway closed. congratulations @bayleebrewer23 send me a dm to claim your prize!

text:
“dream crazier”, el anuncio patrocinado por @nike y narrado por @serenawilliams que conmovió a muchos durante la ceremonia de ayer de los premios #grammys 🌟
.
celebrando a todas las mujeres en el mundo (deportistas o no) que, con su “locura”, han roto barreras.
.
el anuncio resalta la discriminación que sufrimos y hemos sufrido en la historia de la humanidad por exhibir emociones, creencias religiosas, por ser madres, por desafiar percepciones... o simplemente por ser mujeres.
.
incluso hoy, aunque las cosas hayan cambiado mucho, aunque hayamos ganado derechos, y aunque podamos alzar nuestra voz, debemos continuar la lucha de la #igualdad 💪 (también llamado feminismo, al cual muchos le dan una mala connotación)
.
por ello, que este video de 90 segundos está atrayendo mucha atención en la internet.
.
aquí les dejamos la traducción de la narración 👇
“si mostramos emoción, nos llaman dramáticas.

si queremos jugar contra hombres, estamos locas.

y si soñamos con la igualdad de oportunidades, estamos delirando.

cuando defendemos algo, estamos desquiciadas.

si somos demasiado buenas, es que tenemos algo malo.

y sin nos enfadamos, somos histéricas, irracionales o, simplemente, estamos locas.

pero una mujer que corría un maratón estaba loca.

una mujer que boxeaba estaba loca.

una mujer encestando una pelota con fuerza, loca.

una mujer entrenando un equipo de la nba, loca.

una mujer compitiendo con hijab, cambiando de deporte, haciendo una pirueta 1080 o ganando 23 grand slams, teniendo un bebé y luego regresando.. loca, loca, loca y loca.

así que si quieren llamarte loca, está bien.

muéstrales lo que las locas pueden hacer”.
.
#somostoptraining #transformatuvida #topcasa #gym #gimnasio #nike #dreamcrazier #crazy #metoo #niunamenos #miracomonosponemos #equality #womensrights #derechoshumanos #feminist #feministas #feminismo #feminismo #derechosdelamujer #venezuela #caracas

text_retweet:
#repost @lindsaygonzalezyoga
• • • • • •
“no one ever said it would be easy but they definitely said it will be transformational!” i said this countless times throughout the last month to the women in my training and today in meditation i kept saying it to myself. .
.
this last month was one of the most testing months of my career. i led most of the 180 hours of ytt, distributed medication when people were sick, made tough decisions, listened to hardships and shared my own. in addition to offering emotional support i feel responsible for the groups safety. we are sandwiched between a country with natural disasters and a country with political turmoil. i was scared.
let me start by saying...everyone and everything is ok.
.
i struggle too. i second guess myself and i make mistakes. i ask myself the question, “am i good enough?” a lot! it’s through teaching that i’ve found my greatest healing and i’ve seen the transformation with hundreds of people. when i hear a students story, i am often saying #metoo . you are not alone and it gets better.
.
.
it does. it gets better because we are resilient and we are here for the transformation...not because it’s easy. this is the path to self-realization. .
.
i’m so grateful to everyone who supported me this month so i could continue my passion for leading ytt! .
.
. @jackson.takes.photos .

moa martinson utropades till landsmoder av tage erlander 1954, men hennes liv och författarskap formades av fattigdom och patriarkala strukturer. 
i dokumentären "moa martinsson – landsmodern", som blev så populär under göteborgs filmfestival att extraförställningar fick sättas in, gör den stridbara filmaren och aktivisten maj wechselmann ett ambitiöst försök att nyansera bilden av makarna martinson. alla wechselmanns filmer präglas av socialt patos, kraftfullt politiskt engagemang och en personlig blick. detsamma gäller när hon nu, tillsammans med ebba witt-brattström, skildrar en av förra seklets mest betydelsefulla författare och en självklar frontfigur för kvinnokampen i sverige. genom att hämta inspiration och berättelser från sitt eget liv vände sig martinson mot en ny och tidigare negligerad läsekrets – arbetarklassens kvinnor.

välkomna att uppmärksamma internationella kvinnodagen med att se filmen om moa martinsson, vår första #metoo.

text:
our board has added four new members, and we couldn’t be more excited! 
our new board of directors includes authors, scientists, religious leaders, scholars of ethics, and a climate change leader. together, they have professional expertise and experience helping people and animals in canada, china, india, nigeria, rwanda, tanzania, the united kingdom, and the united states.

one of our recruitment priorities was candidates’ commitment to promoting the values of diversity, equity and inclusion in our organization, and in the work we do to fight factory farming. our new board composition also better reflects the #gender and #racial diversity of the communities we work in and with. follow along this week to learn more about each of these leaders in their respective fields!

text:
join anos on friday 1st of march for a special anos in partnership with crystal palace foundation for life.
our subject this month is “are men in the community doing enough to be allies for women in the quest for equality/justice?”
in light of the historical allegations regarding harvey weinstein, r kelly and bill cosby and the muted condemnation in some quarters, some are asking the question are men in the community doing enough to be allies to women?
other topics that will be touched on as a part of the larger discussion:

should every woman who makes an allegation of sexual assault automatically be believed without the burden of proof as suggested by the #metoo movement or is this an overcorrection of women not being believed in the past.
what steps can men in the community help to facilitate, to better support victims of historical sexual abuse, educate young men and empower young women to break the cycle of abuse/inequality?
should an understanding of consent be taught in schools and at what age?
should we be teaching young men to actively call out inappropriate behaviour towards young women amongst their peer groups?
is toxic masculinity worse in ethnic communities than in white communities?
due to the range of topics, we will be sticking to an allotted time frame to discuss each issue.
please feel free to share the details of this event with your peers as you see appropriate.
we look forward to seeing you on the night.
1st march 2019 @19.30hrs – selhurst railway club london se256ns
£5 contributory fee on arrival.

text:
⛔️please read⛔️
may god bless @projectbaby_ng for this message! please read!!!
dear mom of boys,⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
just a friendly reminder that now is the time to raise kind men 🙏🏾🙌🏾⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i am asking you to please talk to your sons about women’s rights, about kindness, about boundaries and limits, teach them to not put up with disrespectful “jokes” about women 🤦🏾‍♀️⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i just heard my 4yo call his nanny “fat” 🤦🏾‍♀️ and even though it may have seemed innocent, it was an opportunity to speak up as a mother, as a woman and as an employer. teach your boys that it isn’t their place to comment on a woman’s body. because of you, they will grow up to take notice of a woman’s smart brain, witty humor or kind heart 💕🥰⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
keep holding your boys responsible for their actions and the outcomes. keep teaching them to keep their hands to themselves. to not resort to violence, to use their words. boys will not be boys! boys will be kind!⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i am asking you to start this now - when they are still little boys; before they get a chance to get their answers online, or from the wrong people. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
let’s raise a generation of men who will read about the #metoo movement in the history books and shake their heads in disbelief.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
dear m.o.b, stay the course 🙌🏾✊🏽✊🏽⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
the ark #metoo tutu color & glow run will be a night to remember with a fun glow in the dark color course & dance party! 
april is sexual assault awareness month, we wish to honor the #metoo movement and continue empowering victims to stand up and be heard, and encourage the community to surround those voices with love and light. 
entries must be received by march 22nd to be guaranteed a t-shirt! 
to get more information or to signup, visit our website & click the event page!
